61C with Garcia is not incredibly difficult information-wise (i.e., problems are generally more straightforward than some of the tricky 61A/B ones) but the class does have a consistently high workload. When I took it, there was always an assignment due and I was basically always working on a homework assignment or project. If you enjoy the material, this isn't a big deal, but for friends of mine who didn't, it can be pretty draining. That being said, whether you enjoy it or not, it's more than manageable if you start assignments early and really hone your time management skills.

In 170 this semester, and I don't necessarily feel that the workload is super high (spend less time on the class than I did with 70), but the problems are certainly much more challenging. Very manageable if you have a consistent study group and/or are happy to spend some time in Office Hours. In my experience though this certainly hasn't been a class that I've been able to just grind out on my own. I also enjoy the material a lot, so working on tougher problems/reading the textbook doesn't feel too draining. 

Can't speak for 188 as I have not taken it, but a handful of my friends have taken it and really enjoyed the material. Projects/HWs aren't too bad, but exams can be pretty tough. 

I think it's doable with good time management, and if you're good at dealing with a constant stream of work. I know a lot of people who have made 61c/170 work. Reiterating that I haven't taken 188 so take my advice with a grain of salt, but I understand that it is generally considered a better upper-div to take early on so probably isn't the worst choice if you're to take a third tech. Hope this helps!

I actually had this exact schedule and thought it was pretty solid. The early parts of 188 and 170 (graph/search) overlap a ton, to the point where learning the material for one course covers 70-80% of the other. Also 188 and 170 are extremely low workload classes, projects for 188 are 61a level, and 170 psets are 3-10 hours per week if you’re up to speed on material. That being said, both classes are relatively difficult conceptually (dont sleep on 188 midterms!). 61C is the polar opposite, pretty easy conceptually, but a solid stream of work. I also took 61C with Garcia, and it was a lot less work than I expected. I also felt 61C and 170 were also oddly complimentary, and it was defiantly cool seeing opposite ends of the CS spectrum.

 I was super nervous about my schedule due to all the horror stories/piazza posts, but it turned out to be surprisingly light. Still had time for friends/screwing around. Just anecdotal experience, but I do generally think people are overly pessimistic about workload on these types of threads. If you think you’re up to it, you probably are
